law.text:
As used in KRS 162.520 to 162.620, the following terms and words have the following respective meanings, unless another meaning is clearly indicated by the context:
As used in KRS 162.540, 162.550, 162.580, 162.590, 162.600, and 162.620 "authority" means "State Property and Buildings Commission;"
"Department" means the State Department of Education;
"Board of education" means the governing body of a county school district, or of an independent school district, for which the authority issues its revenue bonds pursuant to KRS 162.520 to 162.620;
"Project" means any undertaking to provide for a board of education any school buildings, facilities, improvements, and appurtenances authorized in KRS 162.120 to 162.300;
"Lease" or "lease instrument" means a written instrument for the leasing of one (1) or more school projects executed by the authority as lessor and a board of education as lessee, conforming to the specifications set forth in KRS 162.140;
"Bonds" or "bonds of the authority" means bonds issued by the authority under KRS 162.520 to 162.620, payable as to principal and interest solely from rentals received from a board of education pursuant to a lease.
